I think writing the anthros as being psychologically different from humans would be quite interesting.

A lot of our biology and physiology came from evolving as hunters on the african steppe. A herbivore doesn't really need brainpower to eat plants but brainpower's necessary to hunt. Communication evolved to make hunting more efficient, a large part of our brain is dedicated to vision, giving us good awareness of our surroundings. In fact we're damn lucky we're omnivorous, if we were carnivorous, our societies would look a lot like the steppe people of central asia.

Maybe that could be used in a story with lots of predatory anthros having nomadic tribal societies and always messing up sedentary farming humans, who just can't get to a critical food production point.

Basically
mongols = anthros
people that got fucked up by mongols = humans
europe = uninhabitable
